'''Alberto Alemán Zubieta''' (born c. 1951) is a former administrator of the [[Panama Canal]]. He graduated from [[Texas A&M University]] in civil and industrial engineering in 1973. He lives in Panama with his wife, Ana Matilde, and their three children.<ref>http://www.pancanal.com/eng/general/junta-directiva/aleman.html</ref><ref>http://international.tamu.edu/BoardBios/Alem%C3%A1nZubieta.pdf</ref><ref>http://smu.edu/newsinfo/stories/panama-canal-ceo.asp?print=true</ref><ref>http://www.panama-guide.com/article.php/20071214142557204</ref>
== Awards == * "William Ross Medal", presented in 1992 by the Panamanian Chamber of Construction (CAPAC) * "Honorary Fellow" in 1997 and "Federal Engineer of the Year Award" from the [[American Society of Civil Engineers]] * "Florencio Icaza Award" bestowed by the Association of Panamanian Architects and Engineers (SPIA) * "Maritime Personality 2001" Award, presented by Seatrade * "The Business man of the Year 2002" from the Panamanian Business Executives Association (APEDE) * "Outstanding International Alumnus Award of Texas A&M University" awarded in December 2003
