The '''National U.S.–Arab Chamber of Commerce''' (NUSACC) is America’s oldest [[chamber of commerce]] dedicated to US-Arab business.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nusacc.org/about-us.html|title=About Us|website=National U.S.-Arab Chamber of Commerce|access-date=2017-01-13}}</ref> In 2016, the organization won the 2016 [[President of the United States]]’ “E” Award for Export Service, marking the first occasion that the award went to an entity dedicated to US-Arab relations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.commerce.gov/news/secretary-speeches/2016/05/us-commerce-secretary-penny-pritzker-address-2016-presidents-e-and-e|title=U.S. Commerce Secretary Penny Pritzker Address at the 2016 President’s “E” and ”E-Star” Awards Ceremony|date=2016-05-16|newspaper=Department of Commerce|access-date=2017-01-13}}</ref> [[David Hamod]] is the organization's President and CEO.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.washdiplomat.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=14050:chamber-of-commerce-head-brings-us-arab-world-together&catid=1548&Itemid=428|title=Chamber of Commerce Head Brings U.S., Arab World Together|last=bwm-admin|website=www.washdiplomat.com|access-date=2017-01-13}}</ref>

