'''Sampo Karjalainen''' (born May 2, 1977) is one of the original founders of [[Sulake]] and [[Habbo Hotel]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CX5UAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Sampo+Karjalainen%22+habbo&dq=%22Sampo+Karjalainen%22+habbo&hl=en&ei=7CvUTfCfB-fbiALpwNTAAg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CEkQ6AEwAw|title=Ars Electronica|year=2001|work=Flash art, Issues 219-221|page=59|accessdate=18 May 2011}}</ref> an online social networking video game aimed at teenagers. Sampo has also been in other projects, including Bobba Bar for iPhone.{{citation needed|date=October 2012}} Karjalainen is now the designer, [[chief executive officer]], and co-founder of ProtoGeo Inc., the creators of the Moves fitness tracker app for [[iOS]].<ref>https://techcrunch.com/2013/01/24/moves-app-activity-tracker/</ref>

He studied literature, theoretical physics and information processing at the [[University of Helsinki]].{{citation needed|date=August 2013}}

