'''Simon Currant''', [[Honorary Member of the Order of Australia|AM]] is a tourism developer in [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]]. Currant currently serves as a director of the Tourism Council of Tasmania and a Director of [[TT-Line Pty. Ltd.]]<ref>[http://www.tourismtasmania.com.au/org/board/index.html Tourism Tasmania Board Information] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080719003730/http://tourismtasmania.com.au/org/board/index.html |date=2008-07-19 }}</ref>
His past tourism developments include the Strahan Village, Cradle Mountain Lodge, [[Peppermint Bay]] and [[Pumphouse Point Tasmania|Pumphouse Point]].
He was awarded a [[Centenary Medal]] in 2001,<ref>{{cite news |title=It's an Honour |url=http://www.itsanhonour.gov.au/honours/honour_roll/search.cfm?aus_award_id=1122119&search_type=simple&showInd=true |work=Australian Government Honour Roll |date=2001-01-01 |accessdate=2008-10-22 }}</ref> [[Tasmanian of the Year]] in 2004<ref>{{cite news |title=Victory surprises Tasmanian of the Year |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2004/03/13/1065230.htm |work=ABC |date=2004-03-13 |accessdate=2008-05-29 }}</ref> and appointed an honorary Member of the [[Order of Australia]] in 2006.<ref>{{cite news |title=It's an Honour |url=http://www.itsanhonour.gov.au/honours/honour_roll/search.cfm?aus_award_id=1129455&search_type=simple&showInd=true |work=Australian Government Honour Roll |date=2006-03-13 |accessdate=2008-05-29 }}</ref>
